cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper is about evaluating cross-lingual word embeddings, which is a topic related to natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of modularity, a network measurement, which is related to machine learning and graph theory, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of unsupervised learning and validation metrics, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR), respectively.
